cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this repository, please cite the companion paper (preferred-citation below)."

title: "commit-confluence: reproducibility artifact for a pre-registered study of commit-moment hallucination signals"
abstract: >-
  Pre-registration, gated evaluation data, registered per-deployment score matrices and
  calibration profiles, and analysis code for a study of whether four families of
  commit-moment internal signals (attention morphology, residual motion, readout geometry,
  and output confidence) unify into one calibrated detector, and whether that detector is
  universal or must be calibrated per deployment. Scope note: the evaluated task is
  candidate-answer correctness readout (YES/NO judgment of a supplied candidate) on ten
  4-bit open-weight models of 1.7B-8B across two benchmarks, not detection of spontaneous
  hallucination in free generation.

type: software
